	<item>
		<title>Girls Outshine Boys in Class X Board Examination</title>
		<link>http://tibet.net/2015/06/girls-outshine-boys-in-class-x-board-examination/</link>
		<comments>http://tibet.net/2015/06/girls-outshine-boys-in-class-x-board-examination/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2015 09:59:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Tenzin Yangchen]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[News Flash]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Uncategorized]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tibet.net/?p=75989</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[DHARAMSHALA: The Central Board Secondary Education (CBSE) on 28 May declared the result of Class X students. 1472 students from 27 various Tibetan schools have participated in the exams held this March. This year Class X CBSE result indicated the &#8230; <a href="http://tibet.net/2015/06/girls-outshine-boys-in-class-x-board-examination/">Continued</a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pf-content"><p>DHARAMSHALA: The Central Board Secondary Education (CBSE) on 28 May declared the result of Class X students. 1472 students from 27 various Tibetan schools have participated in the exams held this March.</p>
<p>This year Class X CBSE result indicated the performance of Tibetan schools comparatively less progressive.</p>
<p>Out of the 1472 Tibetan students who appeared in the exam, 1423 students have passed. This year the overall pass percentage of Tibetan schools is 96.67%, which is 2.59% less compared to the last year&#8217;s over all pass percentage of 99.26%. Among the 27 Tibetan schools, 16 schools have got 100% pass percentages.</p>
<p>Like previous year’s results, girls have performed better in the Class X examination this year as well. The overall pass percentage of boys this year was 95.35% whereas the overall pass percentage of girls was 99.60%.</p>
<p><a href="http://tibet.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Result2015-3.xls">Click here</a> to view the Summary of 2015 Class X CBSE exam results of Tibetan schools in India.</p>
<p><em>-Report filed by Department of Education, CTA.</em></p>
</div>]]></content:encoded>
