		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://tibet.net/?p=75984</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[DHARAMSHALA: The Tibetan Parliament in Exile has appointed the 7th Public Accounts Committee (PAC) members. The members of the PAC are Mr. Pema Jungney, Gazi Geshe Tse ringpo, Mr. Gyarig Thar, Ms. Yangchen Dolker and Ms. Ghang Lhamo. Mr. Pema &#8230; <a href="http://tibet.net/2015/06/7th-public-accounts-committee-commences-its-work/">Continued</a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pf-content"><div id="attachment_75985" style="width: 500px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://tibet.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/DSC04161.jpg" class="jackbox cta_post_image" style="display:block" data-group="images" data-thumbnail="http://tibet.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/DSC04161.jpg" >
<img class="size-full wp-image-75985 img-responsive " src="http://tibet.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/DSC04161.jpg" alt="The 7th PAC members at work" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The 7th Public Accounts Committee members at work.</p></div>
<p>DHARAMSHALA: The Tibetan Parliament in Exile has appointed the 7<sup>th</sup> Public Accounts Committee (PAC) members.</p>
<p>The members of the PAC are Mr. Pema Jungney, Gazi Geshe Tse ringpo, Mr. Gyarig Thar, Ms. Yangchen Dolker and Ms. Ghang Lhamo. Mr. Pema Jungney and Mr. Gyarig Thar were unanimously elected as the committee chairman and secretary respectively. The Speaker and Deputy Speaker of the parliament have issued advisory to the committee, who has commenced its work from 1 June.</p>
<p>The 7<sup>th</sup> PAC will table its report at the 11<sup>th</sup> session of the 15<sup>th</sup> Tibetan Parliament in Exile through the Parliament Secretariat.</p>
</div>]]></content:encoded>
